  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "## Description\r\nRunning Lighthouse with `--port 0` causes a permissions error and then fails to startup. Manually assigning the quic port or using `--disable-quic` resolves the error.\r\n\r\nThis occurs since [by default, the quic port is set as as `port + 1`.](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/unstable/beacon_node/src/config.rs#L971). When using `--port 0`, we are telling the operating system to choose a free port, however by doing so, the quic port is then set to `0 + 1`.\r\n\r\nOnly the `root` user is able to bind to ports which are <1024 and thus we get a permissions error.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nOne solution would be to add a larger offset such that the port gets bound to above `1024`.\r\n\r\nAnother solution would be to assign the quic port to 0 if the `port` is also 0. `if port == 0 { quic_port = 0 }`",
